{
  "description": "Shared webhook-signing test vectors (SLO-128). Generated from the PRODUCTION signing code in sloth-box/api (lib/webhookSigning + lib/webhookPublish). Checked into sloth-box/api (src/lib/webhookSigningVectors.json) and sloth-box/sdk-typescript (src/webhook-signing-vectors.json); both test suites consume it so the signer and the SDK verifier cannot drift apart silently. Do not edit by hand — regenerate with `npm run vectors:webhooks` in sloth-box/api.",
  "scheme": "Standard Webhooks v1 (svix-compatible): webhook-signature is `v1,base64(HMAC-SHA256(key, `${webhook-id}.${webhook-timestamp}.${rawBody}`))` where key = base64-decode of the secret after stripping the whsec_ prefix. During rotation the header is a space-delimited token list; any v1 match is valid. Receivers reject timestamps more than toleranceSeconds from now (strictly greater than, both directions).",
  "toleranceSeconds": 300,
  "cases": [
